ry handling**\\n\\nI’m considering the secure variant where reading the NoSuchFile attribute returns zeros, which seems positive. I’m also thinking about using newSecureDirectoryStream for the current directory temp. If it doesn’t have secure directories, I need to assert that it’s unsupported, but I shouldn’t short-circuit the process. It feels crucial to ensure that everything operates smoothly, even if there’s a lack of secure directories. I need to approach this carefully to avoid any potential mishaps!\\n\\n**Considering temp directory cleanup**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the Files2.deleteRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure function in @TempDir, particularly how it deletes the root. If @TempDir isn't cleaned up, that might be a problem. I'll need to make sure any created directories are cleaned up since TempDir handles this. Also, if creating a symlink fails due to permissions, I need to consider how to handle that without failing. It might be better to catch IOExceptions quietly. I’ll need to test precisely when a symlink is created and how that affects stats.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0bf73612ac7d5bfc0169f395f061b08195a7139fa6aeaf6eae\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp85YHLoYH54GSMdhvCcF0kPZ4pamFsW5nao33BFQIzR4K__XH3eUxphimQ9DNcnMB4S3G_ZC9B0egxN5mrIx8XpJob_OPFUraPELn74Lp1KSTJACOYd7t0OyDOT5RACM_gh5ARBghpBrRcwmwA4uDInxZuO3xRnf_t_hI_xFn8amjp_AQdwOQ1Cx7XtDomBG9iP0Aly88tDCdc0X6RGGR-wurcj418X08Kq_FXtiKO4YyMSddH3M1DRg5oMcoxINKfqPp17FtUX2QZaI9UolwRNQUol3PdxA6W4WObmjT2NRz0BKBqX4wPyxqNskrDJJl6EQtYULc7KzQbHZHJeGmW0WswmXr_Otv1YEPZtTwFlon47KJoCjs-zE9rjRva2nSoEBtzWU2b_-6vgYrqFzZEZEq1yHG2qDjstJuve_vpvc8NvMFXMCY2-mPo8tWDqGnyK-F7yMZhCyq2u4M1691RPA9VGSpDqzVYpDpA80MWm3P5loCJrL9URO8ZZRVzBpUA_UQ_2FLabTwFGshPruAJDj0aDYsApO1tt2EsKBPoP5y5Z3lMTXpx3S8m-E-ip0-cDLdBs9DLVwUWVGkS2Q-dJ-MMdPa7-QIYKjKCROrymLTh4m0dfWZLz2E46habPQ94AEZ015QzX9sulyqe-PiT6mUHpotVy4i5iwsmyDNeGEK4Saz3ydog-GKft5Ki8IwpvYDR1XeaTzvElO_mw43GYh6atR1WeWNGw1TF2CHwZ_DVkjDZIvwGzc